Estimations (by Pillar)

We follow the general model but replacing \(DIG_i\) with all \(k=11\) Pillars. More specifically,

\[\begin{align*} \text{ln } p_{ijk} &= \alpha + \sum_{k=1}^{11} \beta_k Pillar_k + \gamma_1 \rho_k + \gamma_2 \theta_{ij} + \gamma_3 tariff_{ijk} \\ & + \gamma_4 NTM_{ijk}^{Tech} + \gamma_5 NTM_{ijk}^{Non-Tech} + \gamma_{6i}(NTM_{ijk}^{Tech} \times \delta_i) + \gamma_{7i}(NTM_{ijk}^{Non-Tech} \times \delta_i) + \gamma_8 sim_{ij} + \epsilon_{ijk} \end{align*}\]

library(dplyr)

reporter.aves <- aves.dta %>% 
  group_by(reporteriso3) %>% 
  summarise(ave_weighted= weighted.mean(NNeg.BP1, tradevalue, na.rm = TRUE))

reporter.aves$names <- c("Australia", "Brunei", "China", "Hong Kong", "India", "Indonesia", "Japan", "Cambodia",
   "Korea, Rep.", "Kazakhstan", "Lao", "Malaysia", "Nepal", "New Zealand", "Pakistan",
   "Phillipines", "Russia", "Singapore", "Thailand", "Turkey", "Vietnam", "Vanuatu")
reporter.aves$grp <- c(3, 3, 2, 3, 2, 2, 3, 1, 3, 2, 1, 2, 1, 3, 1, 2, 2, 3, 2, 3, 1, 1)

reporter.aves<-reporter.aves[!(reporter.aves$ave_weighted=="NaN"),]

library(ggplot2)

ggplot(data = reporter.aves, aes(x = grp, y = ave_weighted, fill = reporteriso3)) +
    geom_bar(stat="identity", position ="dodge") +
    geom_text(aes(label= reporteriso3), vjust= 1.3, size=3.5) +
    theme_minimal()
